TY  - JOUR
T1  - Note—Controlling Inventories in an Acyclic Assembly System
AU  - Tang, Christopher S.
Y1  - 1992/05/01
PY  - 1992
DA  - 1992/05/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.38.5.743
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.38.5.743
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 743
EP  - 750
VL  - 38
IS  - 5
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This note presents a model of an acyclic assembly system that faces yield loss and uncertain demand. While there is no known production rule for managing acyclic systems, we develop a production rule whose operating characteristics could be measured analytically. Thus, the operating characteristics can be used as a benchmark for future comparison. To facilitate our analysis, we extend the model for a serial production system that produces a single product (Tang 1990). This extension entails a modification of the production rule and the analysis of a decomposition scheme.
AB  - This note presents a model of an acyclic assembly system that faces yield loss and uncertain demand. While there is no known production rule for managing acyclic systems, we develop a production rule whose operating characteristics could be measured analytically. Thus, the operating characteristics can be used as a benchmark for future comparison. To facilitate our analysis, we extend the model for a serial production system that produces a single product (Tang 1990). This extension entails a modification of the production rule and the analysis of a decomposition scheme.
