TY  - JOUR
T1  - Note—Project Selection and Sequencing to Maximize Net Present Value of the Total Return
AU  - Gupta, Sushil K.
AU  - Kyparisis, Jerzy
AU  - Ip, Chi-Ming
Y1  - 1992/05/01
PY  - 1992
DA  - 1992/05/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.38.5.751
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.38.5.751
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 751
EP  - 752
VL  - 38
IS  - 5
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This note considers a problem of simultaneous selection of a subset of N projects and determination of an optimal sequence to implement these projects so as to maximize the net present value of the total return. We first establish an optimal sequence of all projects which does not depend on the particular subset of selected projects and then propose an efficient polynomial dynamic programming method for solving the problem.
AB  - This note considers a problem of simultaneous selection of a subset of N projects and determination of an optimal sequence to implement these projects so as to maximize the net present value of the total return. We first establish an optimal sequence of all projects which does not depend on the particular subset of selected projects and then propose an efficient polynomial dynamic programming method for solving the problem.
